      <h2>Important Considerations for Side Hustles</h2>

      <h3>Tax Implications</h3>
      <p>Any income earned from a side hustle is generally taxable. This includes both income tax and self-employment tax. It's highly recommended to keep your personal and business finances separate, track all your income and expenses meticulously, and consult with a tax professional to ensure you're setting aside enough for quarterly estimated taxes.</p>

      <h3>Time Management Tips</h3>
      <p>Balancing a side hustle with a full-time job or other responsibilities requires excellent time management. Utilize time-blocking to dedicate specific, uninterrupted hours to your hustle. Prioritize high-impact tasks and learn to say no to distractions. Most importantly, schedule time for rest to prevent burnout—consistency is more sustainable than overworking yourself in short bursts.</p>

